Spanish Stocks: Banco Pastor, Sacyr, Mapfre Shares Move

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-02-11T16:49:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/spanish-stocks-sacyr-mapfre-fergo-aisa-shares-move-in-madrid.html
Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index  advanced for a
first day in three, adding 11.7, or 0.1 percent, to 10,803.6 at
the 5:30 p.m. close in Madrid. The gauge has dropped 0.5 percent
this week. The Madrid Stock Exchange General Index advanced 0.2
percent today.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.    Banco Pastor SA  (PAS SM) climbed 1.2 percent to 3.94 euros,
breaking six days of losses. The Spanish bank that traces its
roots to 1776 reported its 2010 profit fell 39 percent to 62.1
million euros from 101.1 million euros a year ago, it said in a
filing to regulators today. The lender will seek to double
profit by 2013 and have a core capital ratio in that year of 9.8
percent, it said.    Mapfre SA  (MAP SM) dropped 0.8 percent to 2.65 euros, a
fourth straight loss. Spain’s biggest insurer sold its Masters
II building in Madrid for 113.5 million euros to Spain’s
government-run Consorcio de Compensacion de Seguros, Expansion
reported, without citing anyone.    Sacyr Vallehermoso SA  (SYV SM) jumped for a third day,
advancing 6.2 percent to 7.7 euros, the stock’s highest price in
more than a year. The Spanish builder said it won a road-
cleaning and waste-collection contract worth 34.2 million euros
in Plasencia, Spain.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:  David Merritt  at 
 dmerritt1@bloomberg.net . 